# Functions Rules

- Runtime target: Node.js 22, Firebase Functions 1st gen (`firebase-functions/v1`).
- Region: `us-central1` unless intentionally changed. Note: Firestore is in `northamerica-northeast1` — every call is cross-region. Do not add new functions in other regions without discussing trade-off.
- Google Wallet: use Application Default Credentials (ADC) only. GCP org policy blocks JSON key files — never attempt that path.
- Production logging is allowed in functions (`console.log/warn/error`) for observability.
- Validate redirect URLs and external input; never trust request payload blindly.
- Keep API auth/authorization checks intact (`verifyIdToken`, admin gate via `admins` collection).
- Prefer additive, backward-compatible changes to function payloads and scheduled jobs.
- Before deploy, verify for orphan functions and clean intentionally:
  `firebase functions:delete <orphan-name> --region us-central1 --force`
- Currently deployed (7): `api`, `contactForm`, `onWalletPassRequest`, `aggregateTaps`, `aggregateCampaignTaps`, `cleanupInactiveTenants`, `seedDemoData`. For live state, check `CLAUDE_HANDOFF.md` or run `firebase functions:list`.
- `/c/:cardId` is handled client-side by the `CardRedirect` React component + Firestore lookup. Do not re-introduce a public HTTPS function for this — blocked by GCP org policy.